Now, the code's array is 1-based, so when we write c(n+2 -i), the indices are correctly 1-based. Also, in the loop variable, in Fortran, in the loop do i = 2, n+1 → runs from 2,...,n+1. Now, in the Java code, the loop is:

for (int i=2; i <=n+1; i++)

So same as Fortran. Thus all indices look okay.
